Prohibition, Excise &
Registration Dept., Vikas Bhawan, Bailey Road,
Patna, Bihar-800015.
Accept All Term and Condition as per Rfp & NIT
EMD Bank Guarantee/Reciept done online. MSME will be exempted from paying EMD. The revised Bank Guarantee is 1%

Legal Entity Certificate of Incorporation
Partnership Deed/Legal documents  for existence of the firm/enitity as applicable
Turnover Certificate from Statutory Auditor confirming the same
Work Experience  Of Work order/completion certificate.
EMD of INR 50,000 (Fifty thousand only) to be submitted. MSME will be exempted from paying EMD. The revised Bank Guarantee is 1%
The Bidder should be a sole Proprietorship firm, a Partnership firm or company registered under Indian Companies Act 1956 .
The bidder should be GST registered
The bidder should provide valid PAN number
The bidder in its name must have achieved a minimum average annual financial overall turnover of minimum INR 5lacs per year for the last three years.
The agency should have prior  experience in providing sniffer dog and handlers to the clients.
The accommodation for Dog and handlerboth shall be provided by the department
The revised timelines for providing dogs will be 4 weeks from the issue of work order.

Bidder should train dogs in such a way
that they can detect alcohol 4 feet or more
below the ground.

Local authority will provide alcohol
whenever needed for the training
purpose.

JV and Partnership can participate in the
tender. The requited JV/Partnership certificate should be submitted along with the bid response.
MSME will be exempted from paying EMD.

Bidder shall provide all relevant medical
certificates like vaccine certificates,
Medical fitnesss certificate to name a few
to the Department.
Department reserves right that the
Animal Husbandry office will check the medical certificates including immunization of dogs.

Local authority will provide onsite
training to dogs on regular basis.
Bidder should get medical checkups done
of the dogs and handler every 6 months at
their own cost as per RFP.
The vaccination and maintenance of the
dogs is the entire responsibility of the
bidder.
